properties.Title: Blizzard Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Blizzard conditions are expected until tomorrow over some areas of Nunavik. Conditions will gradually improve this evening over the communities of Umiujaq, Inukjuak, Puvirnituq and Salluit. However, blizzard conditions will persist Monday over Kuujjuarapik, Sanikiluaq and Kangiqsujuaq. A blizzard warning is issued when winds are expected to produce blowing snow with widespread visibilities of 400 metres or less for at least 6 hours. ### Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to QCstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #QCStorm.

properties.Title: Frost Advisory In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Frost may damage some crops in frost-prone areas. Temperatures will drop near the freezing mark or slightly below overnight. In addition, the unseasonably relatively cool weather will continue for several more days. Accordingly, frost advisory over Southwestern Quebec could be continued over the following nights and mornings through Wednesday morning or even Thursday in some areas. ### Frost advisories are issued when temperatures are expected to reach the freezing mark during the growing season, leading to potential damage and destruction to plants and crops. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to QCstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #QCStorm.

properties.Title: Blizzard Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Blizzard conditions with poor visibility in snow and blowing snow are expected or occurring. These winds are producing extensive blowing snow with visibilities reduced to 400 metres or less. Conditions should begin to improve overnight tonight. ### Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada.
